<TITLE> Man arrested with ties to Rousseau killing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 11 (bdnews24.com)  Detectives Monday said they had arrested a person with alleged ties with the killing of Arefin Alam Rousseau, son of army officers. At a press conference, the chief detective of Detective Branch of Police, Abdul Jalil, told reporters that a special team of the intelligence wing of police arrested Sirajul Islam Siraj, 27, in Goshairhat of Shariatpur on June 3. An armed gang on May 24 shot dead Rousseau and looted Tk 4.5 lakh shortly after he withdrew the money from NCC Bank on Satmasjid Road in Dhanmondi. He was the son of Lieutenant Colonel Shafiqul Rahman, a neurosurgeon at the Combined Military Hospital in Dhaka and Lieutenant Colonel Ambari Begum of CMH in Comilla. Jalil said Siraj was taken into a five-day remand for interrogation where he admitted his involvement in the killing. Siraj also named five people who were involved in the killing. He also gave a confessional statement to the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka. Jalil hoped the five suspected criminals would be arrested soon. Police seized a motorcycle in Savar, which was used for the daylight mugging. bdnews
